result.adr_address: 238 Hollywood Rd, Tai Ping Shan, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 238 Hollywood Rd, Tai Ping Shan, Hong Kong
result.name: 238 restaurant

reviews.text: Always excellent food / service / drinks.  It's not close to where I live but always find time to go out of my way to experience.  Looking forward to returning tonight!

Since my friend and I had already eaten dinner, we just wanted to have some drinks here before we head home since this venue was near my friend's apartment. While the server was somewhat friendly, she kept getting our orders wrong. Firstly, we ordered the still water but she gave us a bottle of sparkling water. If I had just said 'water', then it would've been fine. Whatever. But, she actually asked us whether we wanted still or sparkling, and I had clearly stated that we wanted still water yet we ended up with sparkling..? Secondly, the server had gotten us a different cocktail than what my friend had originally ordered, so she had to go and make another. There was a big birthday party dinner going on, but the venue was not full nor crazy busy. For a place that commands not a small chum of money, that kind of ineptitude in something so simple as taking an order right was a real turnoff. Especially when we had to pay 10% service charge!!  lol. Since I didn't order main dishes, I cannot say much about the quality of food. The drinks were nice.
I went there for dinner many times, everything was okay. However, I went to there for lunch today. Overall experience is not good.
Very talented chef! One of the best meals I have had in HK. Everything cooked to perfection. Highly recommend!

A small restaurant serving Dutch and European dishes. Free Wi-Fi available. The restaurant has a good collection of beer and wine. Some of the signature dishes include Bitterballen, Croquette, Homemade Fries. The restaurant has daily set lunch with dishes changing regularly. Popular with Dutch and European expats.
